metadata.name: Olfactory Flow #39
metadata.description:
Olfactory flow field expressions inspired by riso prints and niche perfumes.

/////
Depending on the longevity of the scents, the rendering can take some time.

As soon as the simulation is done (indicated by the subtle texture that appears on top) you can save a 2000x3000px png by pressing 's'.
If you want a high resolution file, please contact me via Twitter (@pxlshrd).

Tip for recent mobile devices: open live view and zoom in while the canvas is drawn.

/////
10 % of the 15 % royalties go to the minter.

metadata.name: Rough Cuts #151
metadata.description:
Abstract generative artwork that explores composition and form by cutting canvas with straight lines. Coded brushwork gives a real-painting look to each piece.

Options:

- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view
- press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to save hi-res PNG images

Created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods, July, 2022.

metadata.name: Momentum #31
metadata.description:
In our new project, we explore the possibilities and tools of generative art. This time we were interested in the aesthetics of particles. When static turns into movement, and the predicted composition becomes spontaneous - the experiment continues.
This project was created with P5.js.
March 2023.
Press 'S' to save a PNG file.

metadata.name: RE/Posizioni #46
metadata.description:
Exactly one year ago I was minting my first fxhash project. 
‚ÄúPosizioni‚Äù was a quick sketch of only 25 editions that I put together to test this new platform and to my great surprise, it was the start of an amazing journey in this space that still continues to amaze me every day. 

‚ÄúRE/Posizioni‚Äù is an ideal continuation of my personal path that started one year ago: I decided to create an animated, glitchy, or even broken piece, something completely different from what I usually do as an artist and as a coder (and probably something I‚Äôm not very good at, forgive me for this :D ).
Even if this NFT crazy world is often uncertain, insecure, or unstable, we need to find a balance no matter how difficult, just as the lines in this artwork try to do.

Going out of my comfort zone, experimenting, or just having fun is what keeps this creative practice enjoyable for me, and it‚Äôs all that matters.

----

- Mouse click to pause the animation
- "s" key to download a png
- "f" key to full screen

Tested on Desktop/Chrome.
See LICENSE.md for more licensing details.

metadata.name: Pixels' Narrative #2
metadata.description:
This generative art project is one of the significant milestone for my gen-art journey.
The more I get used to gen-art coding, the more I enjoy it and make it part of my lifestyle.
	
It is cemented with randomization and playing around with shapes. As the pixel generates random forms with colors and values somehow relates to random thoughts and moments to which humanity enjoy to experience.
I usually get inspiration on significant and even random experience I have in life.
This project for me is personal and marked significant lessons on me as I put my mind to work on it.
Hope to see you around sometime.
	
Please be patient, as it may take for a while to generate.
Once rendered, press 'S' to download.
